Library components can be used while making the new React component

Suggested library component (1/4) : Box - If you're looking for a flexible component to help with low-level layout needs, the Box component might be just what you need. With its customizable styles and props, it can be used to create a wide range of UI elements, from simple containers to complex layout structures.
Suggested usage : To layout the price list items


# Box can be imported into the new component like this:
```tsx
import { Box } from '@gluestack-ui/themed'
```

---

# examples of how Box can be used inside the new component:
```tsx
<Box />
```

---

# full code examples of React components that use Box :
box```
import { Box, Text } from '@gluestack-ui/themed'

const Example = () => (
  <Box bg='$primary500' p='$5'>
    <Text color='white'>This is the Box</Text>
  </Box>
)
```

