Library components can be used while making the new React component

Suggested library component (3/4) : Icon - Icons are often used to enhance the usability and accessibility of digital products by providing users with clear and intuitive visual cues. It serves as an intuitive and easily recognizable way to communicate with users.
Suggested usage : To use for displaying the arrow, check and slash icons


# Icon can be imported into the new component like this:
```tsx
import { Icon } from '@gluestack-ui/themed'
```

---

# examples of how Icon can be used inside the new component:
```tsx
<Icon />
```

---

# full code examples of React components that use Icon :
icon```
import React from 'react'
import {Input, VStack, Icon, SearchIcon, InputIcon, InputSlot, InputField} from '@gluestack-ui/themed'
import {EyeIcon, EyeOffIcon} from 'lucide-react-native'

function InputWithIcon-rounded() {
const [value, setValue] = React.useState('')

  return (
<VStack space="md" w="\$full">
      <Input size={"sm"} variant={"rounded"} isInvalid={false} isDisabled={false} size="sm">
        <InputField onChange={(e: any) => {
      setValue(e.nativeEvent.text);
    }} value={value} placeholder="Enter Text here" />
        <InputSlot pr="\$4">
          <InputIcon as={SearchIcon} />
        </InputSlot>
      </Input>

      <Input {...props} size="md">
        <InputField onChange={(e: any) => {
      setValue(e.nativeEvent.text);
    }} value={value} placeholder="Enter Text here" />
        <InputSlot pr="\$4">
          <InputIcon as={SearchIcon} />
        </InputSlot>
      </Input>

      <Input {...props} size="lg" isDisabled>
        <InputField onChange={(e: any) => {
      setValue(e.nativeEvent.text);
    }} value={value} placeholder="Enter Text here" />
        <InputSlot pr="\$4">
          <InputIcon as={SearchIcon} />
        </InputSlot>
      </Input>

      <Input {...props} size="xl" isInvalid>
        <InputField onChange={(e: any) => {
      setValue(e.nativeEvent.text);
    }} value={value} placeholder="Enter Text here" />
        <InputSlot pr="\$4">
          <InputIcon as={SearchIcon} />
        </InputSlot>
      </Input>
    </VStack>
  );
}

export default InputWithIcon-rounded;
```

The style for this library uses the following ways be careful ans use only the style for this libraryBorder
xs: Represents an extra-small border radius.
sm: Represents a small border radius.
md: Represents a medium border radius.
lg: Represents a large border radius.
xl: Represents an extra-large border radius.
2xl: Represents a twice-extra-large border radius.
3xl: Represents a thrice-extra-large border radius.
full: Represents a full border radius, creating a circular or fully rounded appearance.
